1 [4.] 3. If the juvenile court determines that there is probable cause to believe
2 that the person committed the delinquent act, the juvenile court shall determine
3 whether, based upon clear and convincing evidence and considering the interests
4 of justice and the need for protection of the public, to:
5 (a) Dismiss the charges; or
6 (b) Transfer the case for proper criminal proceedings to any court that would
7 have jurisdiction over the delinquent act if the delinquent act were committed by an
8 adult.
9 [5.] 4. In determining the interests of justice and the need for protection of the
10 public, the juvenile court shall consider:
11 (a) The number, date, nature and gravity of the delinquent acts committed by
12 the person.
13 (b) Whether the delinquent acts involved the use of a weapon, violence or
14 infliction of serious bodily injury.
15 (c) The impact to any victim of the person.
16 (d) The extent to which the person has already received punishment,
17 counseling, therapy or treatment after the commission of the delinquent acts, and
18 the response of the person to any such punishment, counseling, therapy or
19 treatment.
20 (e) The behavior of the person since the date on which the person committed
21 the delinquent acts, including, without limitation, the character, maturity,
22 educational progress and work history of the person.
23 (f) Any evidence that the person engaged in recent threats against any person
24 or expressed the intent to commit a crime in the future.
25 (g) Psychological or psychiatric evidence that indicates a risk of recidivism.
26 (h) Any emotional or mental health condition that existed at the time of the
27 commission of the delinquent act.
28 (i) Any physical conditions that minimize the risk of recidivism, including,
29 without limitation, physical disability or illness.
30 (j) Any other factor the juvenile court finds relevant.
31 [6.] 5. If the case is transferred for criminal proceedings pursuant to this
32 section, the court shall also transfer any other related offense arising out of the
33 same facts as the delinquent act, regardless of the nature of the related offense.
34 [7.] 6. The court to which the case is transferred has original jurisdiction over
35 the person.
36 [8.] 7. A person held in custody pursuant to this section must be held in the
37 state prison, a county or city jail or detention facility for adults and is entitled to
38 bail as established in criminal proceedings.
